4. Prophane People of all Sorts, Drunkards, Swearers, Whoremongers, Adulterers, Sabbath-breakers, Thieves: Don't all theſe ſtorm Hell, and endeavour to take Damnation by Violence, out of the Hands of the Devil? They are as earneſt, as if they wou'd take no Denial;
But they need n't fear, they ſhall have their Wages (ſo continuing) as ſure as God is truth.
• . Cor. 6.9, 20.
